frameDefinitions: A Group is described as having members which are similar or dissimilar to each other.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
This frame concerns  words that express an Object's position on a scale, its Measurement, with respect to some attribute, its Dimension.
A Lessee gains the use of Goods owned by a Lessor by payment to the Lessor.
A Theme moves with respect to a Fixed_location, generally with a certain Periodicity, without undergoing unbounded translational motion or significant alteration of configuration/shape.
A Producer produces a Product from a Resource for commercial purposes. '

listRoleDefinitions: This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose diversity is at issue.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the <fen>Group</fen> is assessed.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Group is diverse or homogenous.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the general area in which diversity occurs or exists.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Dimension</fen> which is measured.  Most LUs in this frame incorporate the <fen>Dimension</fen>.
<fen>Object</fen> identifies the item which is measured along one of its <fen>Dimension</fen>s.
<fen>Measurement</fen> identifies the extent of the <fen>Object</fen> along the specified <fen>Dimension</fen>.
The individual that gains temporary use of the <fen>Goods</fen> by paying the <fen>Lessor</fen>
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is an item which is temporarily exchanged for <fen>Money</fen> in a transaction.
When the event occurs.
The location the renting takes place.
A physical entity that is participating in non-translational motion.
The time at which the <fen>Theme</fen> is in bounded motion.
The location where the bounded motion happens.
The person or company that produces the Product.
The <fen>Product</fen> is produced by the <fen>Producer</fen>.
<fen>Factory</fen> identifies the particular plant where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
This Fe identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the product was produced.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
